In order to update the gh-pages on github

1. remove old files via
    git rm -rf inc src

2. maybe update folder structure in generate_doc.sh and header.html
3. generate new documentation
    sh generate_doc.sh
4. add and commit all files to repository
    git add .
    git commit -am 'update documentation to version '
    git push origin gh-pages


In order to view and test the site locally install jekyll as described in 
https://help.github.com/articles/setting-up-your-github-pages-site-locally-with-jekyll/

Then as described run 
bundle exec jekyll serve
and view
firefox http://127.0.0.1:4000/
